    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>/authors/admin/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 07 Apr 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/authors/admin/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Dr. Chuan-Peng Hu is a post-doc researcher at Neuroimaging Center (NIC), University Medical Center Mainz, Germany. His primary research interest is how people keep resilient in adverse environment (e.g., poverty). He values open, transparency, and reproducibility in research and leads the Chinese Open Science Network.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Grew up in a village near Yangtze River in Hubei, a central province in China, Chuan-Peng loves outdoors, e.g., rock climbing, mountaineering, and hiking. He&amp;rsquo;ve climbed four mountains over 5000 meters and reached about 6 km of the Chola Mountain, Sichuan Province, China in June 2014.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
